BFN 

  [Text] Colombian Foreign Minister Noemi Sanin will arrive 
for an official visit to Cuba on 3 May. This visit reconfirms 
bilateral ties between Bogota and Havana since diplomatic 
relations were reestablished on 28 October 1993. Cuban Foreign 
Minister Roberto Robaina officially visited Colombia on December 
1993. Following Robaina's visit, the executive secretary of the 
Council of Ministers visited Colombia and at the time, several 
commercial agreements were signed. 

